d peoples created new culture. After forced northern Florida Everglades Seminole Wars early 19th century, adapted region able resist removal United States Army. Migrants region wanted develop plantations first proposed draining Everglades 1848, work type attempted 1882. Canals constructed throughout first half 20th century, spurred South Florida economy, prompting land development. In 1947, Congress formed Central Southern Florida Flood Control Project, built 1,400 miles (2,300km) canals, levees, water control devices. The Miami metropolitan area grew substantially time Everglades water diverted cities. Portions Everglades transformed farmland, primary crop sugarcane. Approximately 50percent original Everglades developed agricultural urban areas.[1] Following period rapid development environmental degradation, ecosystem began receive notable attention conservation groups 1970s. Internationally, UNESCO Ramsar Convention designated Everglades Wetland Area Global Importance. The construction large airport 6 miles (9.7km) north Everglades National Park blocked environmental study found severely damage South Florida ecosystem. With heightened awareness appreciation region, restoration began 1980s removal canal straightened Kissimmee River. However, development sustainability concerns remained pertinent region. The deterioration Everglades, including poor water quality Lake Okeechobee, linked diminishing quality life South Florida's urban areas. In 2000 Comprehensive Everglades Restoration Plan approved Congress combat problems. To date, expensive comprehensive environmental restoration attempt history, implementation faced political complications. Contents 1 Names 2 Geology 2.1 Limestone aquifers 2.2 Hydrology 3 Climate 4 Formative sustaining processes 4.1 Water 4.2 Rock 4.3 Fire 5 Ecosystems 5.1 Sawgrass marshes sloughs 5.2 Tropical hardwood hammock 5.3 Pineland 5.4 Cypress 5.5 Mangrove Coastal prairie 5.6 Florida Bay 6 History 6.1 Native Americans 6.1.1 Calusa Tequesta