neath Everglades explained geologic history state. The crust underneath Florida one point part African region supercontinent Gondwana. About 300 millionyears ago, North America merged Africa, connecting Florida North America. Volcanic activity centered eastern side Florida covered prevalent sedimentary rock igneous rock. Continental rifting began separate North America Gondwana 180 millionyears ago.[8] When Florida part Africa, initially water, cooler Jurassic Period, Florida Platform became shallow marine environment sedimentary rocks deposited. Through Cretaceous Period, Florida remained tropical sea floor varying depths.[9] The peninsula covered seawater least seven times since bedrock formed.[10] Limestone aquifers[edit] Fluctuating sea levels compressed numerous layers calcium carbonate, sand, shells. The resulting permeable limestone formations developed 25million 70million years ago created Floridan Aquifer, serves main source fresh water northern portion Florida. However, aquifer lies beneath thousands feet impermeable sedimentary rock Lake Okeechobee southern tip peninsula.[11] Limestone formations South Florida. Source: U.S. Geological Survey Five geologic formations make southern portion Florida: Tamiami Formation, Caloosahatchee Formation, Anastasia Formation, Miami Limestone (or Miami Oolite), Fort Thompson Formation. The Tamiami Formation compression highly permeable light colored fossiliferous sands pockets quartz, 150 feet (46m) thick. It named Tamiami Trail follows upper bedrock Big Cypress Swamp, underlies southern portion Everglades. Between Tamiami Formation Lake Okeechobee Caloosahatchee Formation, named river it. Much less permeable, formation highly calcitic composed sandy shell marl, clay, sand. Water underneath Caloosahatchee Formation typically mineralized. Both Tamiami Caloosahatchee Formations developed Pliocene Epoch.[12][13] Surrounding southern part Lake Okeechobee Fort Thompson Formation, made dense, hard limestone, shells, sand. Rain